author: COMSOL
description: At the resonance frequency, the capacitive coupling between the turns causes the impedance of a coil to transition from inductive to capacitive. This application analyzes the resonance of a 5 turn spiral coil of copper equipped with a thin epoxy varnish insulation layer. The capacitive coupling through the thin varnish layer is modeled using a special boundary condition, thereby avoiding costly volumetric meshing.
label: resonant_spiral_coil_3d.mph
